    <body>
        
        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName><hi rend="print">Down, | Beckenham, Kent.</hi></placeName>
                    <salute>My dear Amy</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I have told M<hi rend="superscript">r</hi> Murray to send by tomorrow’s Post (if possible) a copy of my book on Expression &amp;c to you, as a little mark of my affectionate regard.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>My dear Amy | Yours very sincerely | Ch. Darwin</p>
<p>Some people like pasting an authors hand-writing at beginning so I send the same on next Page<ref target="#foot.f2"/></p> 
                </div>
            </div>
            <div type="tnotes">
                <note xml:id="tnote.n1">1.1 (if possible)] <hi rend="italic">parentheses over commas</hi> </note>
            </div>

            
            
            
            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">John Murray was the publisher of <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref>. Ruck was engaged to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1222.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Francis Darwin</ref> (see <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8308.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to G. H. Darwin, 3 May [1872]</ref> and n. 5); she had also helped CD with his work on earthworms (see letters from Amy Ruck to <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1226.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Horace Darwin</ref>, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8168.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">[20 January 1872]</ref> and <ref target="./DCP-LETT-8193.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">[1 February 1872]</ref>). Ruck’s name appears on CD’s presentation list for <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref> (Appendix V).</note>
            <note xml:id="foot.f2">A section of the second page of the letter has been excised.</note>
        </div>                
    </body>
